Exercise: Customize a Decomposition Tree to Show Box Office Data

Objective:
Lock the "Certificate" node in place.
Change the color of the connector lines between nodes.
Enable expand/collapse by clicking on nodes.
Set the data bars to scale relative to their parent node.

Steps Taken:
Used the Decomposition Tree visual with fields: Certificate → Genre → Director.
Locked the Certificate node to prevent it from being removed or replaced.
Customized the connector lines using the Format pane under "Tree > Connector line color".
Activated drill mode by clicking the ↕️ Drill on click icon above the visual.
Set bar scaling to "Parent" via Format pane > Bars > Options.
